@page "/paragraph"
<PageTitle>Paragraph - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="paragraph">Paragraph</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The P component renders a semantic p element with design-system-aware styling.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;P&gt;This is a paragraph of text rendered through the Saascade component.&lt;/P&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Style</td><td>string?</td><td>Inline styles.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Paragraph text content.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="paragraph-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Paragraph</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Paragraph</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the P component renders as a standard p element and inherits
                Bootstrap's typography reboot styles. Bootstrap sets a consistent bottom margin
                on paragraphs and applies the base font size from the Bootstrap typography
                configuration. You can apply Bootstrap text utility classes such as lead,
                text-muted, or fw-bold through the Specialization or Class parameters.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="paragraph-daisyui">DaisyUI Paragraph</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Paragraph</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the P component renders as a standard p element with DaisyUI's
                base typography styles applied through the Tailwind CSS base layer. DaisyUI's
                text color tokens adapt to the active theme, so paragraph text automatically
                uses the appropriate foreground color without requiring explicit color utilities.
                You can override typography with Tailwind text size and color utilities through
                the Class parameter.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="paragraph-basecoat">Basecoat Paragraph</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Paragraph</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the P component renders as a standard p element styled with
                Tailwind's typography utilities from Basecoat's base configuration. Basecoat
                applies a consistent line height and text size that follows the Tailwind
                typographic scale. You can adjust font size, weight, color, and spacing
                through Tailwind utility classes passed via the Class or Specialization parameters.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("paragraph", "Paragraph"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("parameters", "Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("paragraph-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Paragraph", 2, "bootstrap"),
    new TocItem("paragraph-daisyui", "DaisyUI Paragraph", 2, "daisyui"),
    new TocItem("paragraph-basecoat", "Basecoat Paragraph", 2, "basecoat")
])" />

</div>
